Package: language.selector
Title: Interactive Language Selector Component for Shiny Applications
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Anastasiia", "Kostiv", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "anastasiia.kostiv@blueventures.org")
Description: A React-based language selector component for Shiny applications.
    Provides an interactive UI with country flag icons for switching between
    languages. Features responsive design with desktop horizontal menu and
    mobile modal popup. Built-in flag icons are bundled with the package.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
Imports:
    htmltools,
    reactR,
    shiny
Depends:
    R (>= 4.0)
LazyData: true
URL: https://github.com/Barefoot-Ocean/language.selector
BugReports: https://github.com/Barefoot-Ocean/language.selector/issues
